org.threadly.concurrent.future

Class RunnableFutureCallbackAdapter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.threadly.concurrent.future.RunnableFutureCallbackAdapter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The result object type returned by this future
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    Deprecated. 
    To be removed without replacement, if you use this, open an issue on github

    @Deprecated
public class RunnableFutureCallbackAdapter<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    This class is the adapter between a FutureCallback and a Runnable. Allowing you to supply this implementation as a Runnable as a listener into a ListenableFuture and have it convert the future's result into calls into a FutureCallback.

    Instead of constructing this class, it is usually much easier to call into ListenableFuture.callback(FutureCallback).

    Since:
    3.2.0
